@startuml Corporate Supply Chain Data Access
title **Use Case: Corporate ESG / Scope 3 Reporting (Post-Prototype)**\nA food company accesses aggregated SOC data under strict terms

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #424242
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #9E9E9E
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #F9A825
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #FFF3E0
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #EF6C00
skinparam sequenceDividerBackgroundColor #F3E5F5

actor "Lisa Park\n(ESG Analyst\nat FoodCorp)" as Lisa #FFF3E0
participant "FoodCorp\nEDC Connector" as FC_EDC #E3F2FD
participant "Payment\nSystem" as PAY #F3E5F5
participant "Caney Fork\nEDC Connector" as CF_EDC #E8F5E9
actor "Will Thompson\n(Caney Fork)" as Will #E8F5E9

== Setup ==

note over Will, CF_EDC
  Caney Fork publishes SOC data with
  **corporate-partners** access policy and
  **supply-chain-terms** contract policy:
  - Access: corporate / certification-body only
  - Purpose: Scope 3, ESG, certification only
  - Payment: $1,000 USD minimum
  - Anonymisation to regional level mandatory
  - 12-month retention limit
  - Attribution required
  - No redistribution (including subsidiaries)
end note

== Catalog Discovery ==

Lisa -> FC_EDC : Browse Caney Fork catalog
FC_EDC -> CF_EDC : DSP Catalog Query

group Access Policy: corporate-partners
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : membership == "active" ? **YES**
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : participantType in\n["corporate","certification-body",\n"supply-chain-partner"] ? **YES**
  note right of CF_EDC
    FoodCorp is an active corporate member.
    => SOC data offer is **VISIBLE**
  end note
end

CF_EDC --> FC_EDC : Catalog with SOC data offer
FC_EDC --> Lisa : Shows offer with supply-chain terms

note over Lisa
  Lisa reviews the terms:
  - $1,000 per dataset
  - Must anonymise to regional level
  - Must attribute GLCDI in ESG report
  - Data deleted after 12 months
  - Cannot share with subsidiaries
  - Purpose: Scope 3 reporting only
end note

== Payment ==

Lisa -> PAY : Initiates payment ($1,000)
PAY --> Lisa : Payment confirmed\n(reference: PAY-2026-0847)

== Contract Negotiation ==

Lisa -> FC_EDC : Accept terms\npurpose = "Scope3Reporting"\npaymentRef = "PAY-2026-0847"
FC_EDC -> CF_EDC : Contract negotiation

group Contract Policy: supply-chain-terms
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : purpose in ["Scope3Reporting",\n"ESGCompliance",\n"CertificationVerification"] ? **YES**
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : elapsedTime <= 12 months ? **YES** (new)
  CF_EDC -> PAY : Verify payment PAY-2026-0847
  PAY --> CF_EDC : Payment verified ($1,000)
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : payAmount >= $1,000 ? **YES**
  note right of CF_EDC
    All constraints satisfied.
    => **AGREED**
  end note
end

CF_EDC --> FC_EDC : Contract FINALIZED
FC_EDC --> Lisa : Contract confirmed

== Data Transfer ==

Lisa -> FC_EDC : Request transfer
FC_EDC -> CF_EDC : DSP Transfer
CF_EDC --> FC_EDC : SOC measurements dataset

== Lisa uses the data ==

note over Lisa #FFF3E0
  **Lisa's obligations (contractual + governance-level):**

  1. **Anonymise** immediately:
     - Remove "Caney Fork Farms" → "Tennessee Region"
     - GPS coords → county-level aggregation
     - Field IDs → removed

  2. **Attribute** in ESG report:
     "Soil carbon data sourced via GLCDI
      Data Space from participating producers."

  3. **Do not share** raw data with
     FoodCorp subsidiaries or third-party
     analytics firms

  4. **Delete all copies** by month 12
     and confirm deletion to Caney Fork

  5. Use **only for Scope 3 reporting**
     — not for supplier negotiations,
     marketing claims, or resale
end note

== 12 months later: Retention limit ==

/ note over Lisa, CF_EDC
  **Month 12: Retention period expires**
end note

FC_EDC -> Lisa : Reminder: retention period expiring
Lisa -> Lisa : Delete all data copies\nand derivatives
Lisa -> FC_EDC : Confirm deletion
FC_EDC -> CF_EDC : Deletion confirmation\nfrom FoodCorp
CF_EDC --> Will : Notification: FoodCorp\nconfirmed data deletion

note over Will
  Will receives confirmation that
  FoodCorp has deleted his data.
  If FoodCorp needs continued access,
  a **new contract** must be negotiated
  (with a new payment).
end note

@enduml
